caption:
We all know someone who seems weirdly OK with climate change. It can be hard to fathom when the state of the world is keeping you up at night.

Apparently people are more likely to engage when they hear the facts from their friends and family (really, scientists have done research on this). So we asked around to see what our team is coming up against from their loved ones. #EarthDay

caption:
Every day, more than 1 million trees are cut down to make traditional toilet paper. We knew it was a lot, but even we were shocked by how staggering this number turned out to be. ⁠
⁠
How did we get to this? Well, we commissioned a report from an environmental third party about the impact of traditional TP on the planet. If you're interested in the graphs and big numbers, you can read it at the link in our bio. ⁠
⁠
Our bums hold the power to make change, so share this news with someone you know who still wipes with trees!⁠

caption:
The #IPCC released their final report on the climate crisis this week and there’s no getting around it - governments have to step up and take urgent action.  But instead of feeling powerless, we’re choosing to focus on one recommendation that’s within our control: eating less meat. ⁠
⁠
If you’re already meat-free, now’s the time to share your wisdom! What were your biggest hurdles to cutting back and how did you push past them? ⁠
⁠
⁠
⁠
⁠
#plantpower #plantbaseddiet #globalwarming #climateaction

caption:
Climate change is already overwhelming enough. But the fact is, things like hurricanes, droughts and rising sea levels have way more of an impact on women. That’s because they’re more likely to live in poverty, have less access to resources and do more labour, like gathering food and water and keeping the household running.⁠
⁠
It’s a scary thought, but we prefer to focus on the positives. Women and girls are pros at leading change and showing resilience - in fact, they’re already at the forefront of the fight for climate justice. They’re starting activist movements, forcing world leaders to pay attention and making sustainable changes within their communities. By educating and empowering women even more, the effects could be massive. As the UN’s Amina Mohammed says: “Women’s leadership is crucial to building a more sustainable world.” #IWD2022⁠

caption:
It’s hard to imagine having to pump water and carry heavy buckets long distance when you’re about to give birth, right? But for many women in rural Kenya that’s the reality. In fact, 25% of healthcare facilities around the world don’t have access to water, which impacts more than 2 billion people.

In the clip above you’ll hear Julius from @lwalacommunity - one of our awesome charity partners who’s working with local Kenyan communities to turn the situation around. It’s a huge deal, and an organisation we’re so proud to support - with your help, of course!

caption:
We don’t know much about romance, but we know a tonne about toilet paper. So when a little lovebird let us know that paper is the traditional first anniversary gift… you must know where we’re going with this.⁠
⁠
If you managed to lock down your main squeeze during the challenging time that was February 2021 - whether you got married, started going steady or finally decided to go Dutch on a Netflix subscription - we’d like to help you celebrate with a lavishly romantic Paper Anniversary Prize Pack.⁠
⁠
What does that include? A buttload of TP, tissues and more! We have 10 up for grabs, and all you have to do to enter is tell us your one line love story in the comments below. (Check out our story highlights if you need some inspo.) ⁠
⁠
Entries close at 6pm AEDT on February 21, 2022. And if you don’t fit the bill, why not tag your friends and give them a chance? Maybe they’ll be kind enough to share their winnings 😉 ⁠
⁠
The boring stuff: Each prize is valued up to AUD$104. Winners will be notified via Instagram on 24/2/22. This competition is in no way sponsored, endorsed, administered by or associated with Instagram. For full T&Cs, head to the link in bio. ⁠
